{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}} <!-- Commented out: [[File:Bcafl.png|right|BCAFL Logo]] --> The '''1990–91 BCAFL''' was the sixth full season of the [[British Collegiate American Football League]], organised by the British Students American Football Association.
==Changes from last season== *With the increase to 19 teams, the four Conferences was merged into Northern & Southern Conferences. *There were three new teams, representing: **[[Aston University]], joining the Southern Conference **[[University of Cambridge]], joining the Southern Conference **[[University of Leeds]], joining the Northern Conference *Newcastle Scholars changed their name to Newcastle Mariners *Sheffield Pirates changed their name to Sheffield Zulus
