'''Fielders Sports Ground''' is a cricket ground in [[Hornchurch]], England.<ref>http://www.londongardensonline.org.uk/gardens-online-record.asp?ID=HVG030</ref> It was formerly part of the grounds of Langtons House and was known as '''Langton Park''' when it was a [[first-class cricket]] ground.
==History== It is located on land that was part of the grounds of [[Langtons|Langtons House]], built in the 18th century.<ref>[http://www.havering.gov.uk/index.aspx?articleid=4709 Havering Borough Council site]</ref> The park, known as Langton Park, was the home of [[Hornchurch Cricket Club]] and was a major venue from 1785 to 1793. At that time, the Hornchurch club was representative of [[Essex county cricket teams|Essex]] as a county.
The earliest recorded first-class match at Langton Park was in May 1785 when Essex played [[Middlesex county cricket teams|Middlesex]] and the last was [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/0/173.html Essex v MCC] in May 1793.<ref name="S&B">[[Arthur Haygarth]], ''Scores & Biographies'', Volume 1 (1744-1826), Lillywhite, 1862</ref> The ground faded from the records as the [[Napoleonic Wars]] progressed and Essex ceased to have a first-class county team.
By 1889, the Hornchurch club had moved from Langtons to nearby [[Grey Towers]].<ref>[http://www.hornchurchcc.org/index.php?module=PostWrap&page=history.htm Hornchurch CC site]</ref> It is still used by the club as a secondary location to [[Harrow Lodge Park]].<ref>http://www.hornchurchcc.org/Location.htm</ref>
