{{Infobox football club | clubname = 11 Bravos | fullname = Onze Bravos do Malembo| nickname = | founded = | ground = Malembo, [[Cabinda Province]], [[Angola]] | capacity = | chairman = | manager = | league = | season = | position = | }}
'''Onze Bravos do Malembo''' is an [[Angola]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in the town of Malembo, [[Cabinda Province]], [[Angola]].<ref>{{pt}}[http://jornaldosdesportos.sapo.ao/28/0/comuna_do_malembo_carece_de_infra-estruturas_desportivas ''Comuna do Malembo carece de infra-estruturas desportivas''] by Joaquim Suami, in ''Jornal dos Desportos'' on March 10, 2010</ref>
The women's team was several times provinvial champion of Cabinda.
They played in the Angolan women's national championship, held from December 13 to 21, 2008, in [[Luena, Moxico Province]], and placed 4th among twelve teams.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/ango-wom08.html | title=Angola 2008 (Women) Campeonato Nacional National championship (fourth edition) | publisher=rsssf.com | accessdate=5 August 2015}}</ref>
