{{coord|03|05|38.09|N|101|36|05.20|E|region:GB_type:landmark|display=title}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Perbadanan Kemajuan Negeri Selangor | nickname = | country = Malaysia | image = | location = [[Kelana Jaya]], [[Petaling Jaya]], [[Selangor]], [[Malaysia]] | establishment = 1991 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = At least 7,532<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/66/66484.html|title=Australia v South Africa, 1998 Commonwealth Games Final|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=7 October 2011}}</ref> | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = | club1 = | date = 7 October | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/17/1334.html Ground profile }}
'''Perbadanan Kemajuan Negeri Selangor Sports Complex''' (erroneously referred as Perbadanan Kemajuan Negari Selangor by cricket records) is a [[Multi-purpose stadium|multi-purpose sports facility]] in [[Kelana Jaya]], [[Petaling Jaya]], Selangor which is used for [[cricket]] and [[Association football|football]]. It is located near [[MBPJ Stadium]]. Its first recorded use for cricket purposes came in 1991 when the ground hosted a match between [[Malaysia national cricket team|Malaysia]] and [[Singapore national cricket team|Singapore]] in the [[Saudara Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/17/1334_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Perbadanan Kemajuan Negari Selangor, Kuala Lumpur|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=7 October 2011}}</ref>
In 1997, the ground held ten matches in the [[1997 ICC Trophy|ICC Trophy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/17/1334_icct.html|title=ICC Trophy Matches played on Perbadanan Kemajuan Negari Selangor, Kuala Lumpur|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=7 October 2011}}</ref> The following year it held its first [[List A cricket|List A]] match when [[Australia national cricket team|Australia]] played [[Canada national cricket team|Canada]] as part of the [[Cricket at the 1998 Commonwealth Games|cricket competition at the 1998 Commonwealth Games]]. Six further List A matches were played there during the games, the last of which saw the final played between Australia and [[South Africa national cricket team|South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/17/1334_a.html|title=List A Matches played on Perbadanan Kemajuan Negari Selangor, Kuala Lumpur|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=7 October 2011}}</ref> This match also saw the highest recorded attendance for a cricket match in Malaysia, with 7,532 witnessing a South African victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/66/66484.html|title=Australia v South Africa, 1998 Commonwealth Games final|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=7 October 2011}}</ref>
